Adding AXI Stream Interfaces
The maximum number of master IDs for an S\_AXI\_NOC port is 28. Therefore, available master ports to declare must be one of {S00\_AXI, S01\_AXI, ..., S27\_AXI}. Note :S\_AXI\_NOC ports are only used for Versal devices. Following these requirements ensures that your exported AXI interconnect master and slave ports ar...
set parVal []
for {set i 2} {$i < 64} {incr i} {
lappend parVal M[format %02d $i]_AXI \
{memport "M_AXI_GP"}
}
set_property PFM.AXI_PORT $parVal [get_bd_cells /axi_interconnect_0]

Adding AXI Stream Interfaces
Following these requirements ensures that your exported AXI interconnect master and slave ports are compatible with the Vitis platform and avoids the use of cascaded interconnects. The following Tcl script defines AXI master ports on AXI Interconnect IP: The following Tcl script defines AXI memory ports with MIG on...
set parVal []
for {set i 1} {$i < 16} {incr i} {
lappend parVal S[format %02d $i]_AXI
{memport "MIG" sptag "Bank0"}
}
set_property PFM.AXI_PORT $parVal [get_bd_cells /smartconnect_0]

