Using SystemVerilog Traffic Generator APIs
The interest of the C++ traffic generator is that you can use and test your HLS kernels as soon as they are created, without having to synthesize them in a .xo file. This allows you to add more and more realism and flexibility to your simulations without having to recreate a .xclbin file. You can also drive traffic...
pl_in0 = adf::input_plio::create("in_classifier", adf::plio_32_bits);
out0 = adf::output_plio::create("out_interpolator", adf::plio_32_bits);

